  86:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_gpio.c ****     (#) To set the level of several pins and reset level of several other pins in
  87:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_gpio.c ****         same cycle, use HAL_GPIO_WriteMultipleStatePin().
  88:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_gpio.c **** 
  89:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_gpio.c ****    (#) To lock pin configuration until next reset use HAL_GPIO_LockPin().
  90:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_gpio.c **** 
  91:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_gpio.c ****     (#) During and just after reset, the alternate functions are not
  92:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_gpio.c ****         active and the GPIO pins are configured in input floating mode (except JTAG
  93:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_gpio.c ****         pins).
  94:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_gpio.c **** 
  95:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_gpio.c ****     (#) The LSE oscillator pins OSC32_IN and OSC32_OUT can be used as general purpose
  96:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_gpio.c ****         (PC14 and PC15, respectively) when the LSE oscillator is off. The LSE has
  97:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_gpio.c ****         priority over the GPIO function.
  98:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_gpio.c **** 
  99:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_gpio.c ****     (#) The HSE oscillator pins OSC_IN/OSC_OUT can be used as
 100:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_gpio.c ****         general purpose PH0 and PH1, respectively, when the HSE oscillator is off.
 101:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_gpio.c ****         The HSE has priority over the GPIO function.
 102:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_gpio.c **** 
 103:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_gpio.c ****   @endverbatim
